TY  - JOUR
T1  - Ability and willingness to service debt as explanation for commercial and official rescheduling cases
AU  - Lee, Suk Hun
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 15
IS  - 1
SP  - 5
EP  - 27
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/02/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(91)90034-J
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669190034J
AB  - This is a study of debt servicing capacities of LDCs. A common characteristic of the large number of such studies is that they use an eclectic list of explanatory variables. Here a set of explanatory variables is obtained from a willingness-to-pay model. Furthermore, earlier studies did not differentiate among different rescheduling cases. Differentiating based on the type of loans rescheduled, empirical tests have been implemented. Results indicate that explanatory variables are highly significant in explaining the occurrence of commercial and official reschedulings. However, a different set of variables has affected rescheduling decisions of borrowers on commercial and official loans.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Debt-equity swaps as bond conversions: implications for pricing
AU  - Blake, David
AU  - Pradhan, Mahmood
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 15
IS  - 1
SP  - 29
EP  - 41
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/02/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(91)90035-K
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669190035K
AB  - This paper demonstrates that debt-equity swaps are equivalent to bond conversions. They can therefore be valued using the conventional valuation formula for convertible bonds, although account must be taken of the minimum duration of the equity investment once a swap has taken place. This implies that the swap involves the substitution of default risk for a combination of equity and exchange rate risk, and this has to be taken into account when valuing the swap. We provide an illustration of the valuation formula.
ER  - 

