AB  - This paper discusses performance evaluation when the analyst has access to the composition of the portfolio. In the U.S., master trustees and custodians have this information. With this assumption the paper derives techniques for evaluating superior performance. The techniques unlike conventional measures can detect superior performance even when the manager is attempting to market time.
